Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

elements.contents:
Our Legacy

The Cube Storage Pioneers
Since 1996

Wasted space is a thing of the past thanks to the ingenious foresight of engineers from a small Norwegian village. Find out how it all started and what AutoStore has planned for the future of order fulfillment.

elements.title: Thoon Kramom (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the 1866 barque Thoon Kramom (pictured) has a replica serving as a floating restaurant?

elements.title: northern green anaconda (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Will Smith took part in the expedition that discovered the northern green anaconda?

elements.title: Mason Morelli (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that at the age of 28, Mason Morelli became the first player in Vegas Golden Knights franchise history to record two points in their National Hockey League debut game?

elements.title: Kīlauea lava cricket (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the Kīlauea lava cricket disappears from a lava field as soon as any plants start to grow there?

elements.title: Chris Armstrong (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that the British political theorist Chris Armstrong has called for a "blue new deal" to secure ecological resilience for the ocean and a just blue economy?

elements.title: Songs from Suicide Bridge (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Songs from Suicide Bridge was recorded in a repurposed tool shed?

elements.title: Hindu Mela (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that several organisers of the Hindu Mela were involved in a secret society that manufactured matchsticks?

elements.title: Michi (Wikipedia — did you know?)
elements.contents: ... that Julian Assange's lawyer argued that the rules set by the Ecuadorian embassy requiring Assange to take care of his pet cat Michi were "denigrating"?
